# Goal Description
Implement a geo-based notification system that triggers when a user passes by or is near an infrastructure project (Tender). The notification will ask the user for reviews or complaints about the infrastructure.

## Proposed Changes

### Backend API
#### [MODIFY] [controllers/tenders.js](file:///f:/Antigravity/Acehack/controllers/tenders.js)
- Add a new controller function `getNearbyTenders` that accepts `lat`, `lng`, and `radius` (default 500 meters) from the query string.
- Will query all active/awarded tenders and calculate the distance using the Haversine formula to return any tenders within the radius.

#### [MODIFY] [routes/tenders.js](file:///f:/Antigravity/Acehack/routes/tenders.js)
- Add a new `GET` route `/nearby` mapped to `getNearbyTenders`. This route will be placed before `/:id` to avoid route conflicts.

---

### Frontend Tracking and UI
#### [NEW] [public/js/geo-notify.js](file:///f:/Antigravity/Acehack/public/js/geo-notify.js)
- Create a new script to handle geolocation tracking.
- Will use `navigator.geolocation.watchPosition` to periodically get the user's current location.
- Will call the `/api/v1/tenders/nearby` endpoint with the location coordinates.
- If a nearby tender is found, it will inject a modern, glassmorphism-styled toast notification on the screen: "You are near [Tender Title]. Any complaints or feedback about this infrastructure?".
- Action buttons will link directly to `/public/complaints.html?tenderId=[id]`.
- Will use `sessionStorage` or local memory to prevent spamming notifications for the same tender multiple times.

#### [MODIFY] [public/index.html](file:///f:/Antigravity/Acehack/public/index.html)
- Include the new `<script src="/js/geo-notify.js"></script>` near the end of the `<body>` so it runs for any visitor landing on the page.

#### [MODIFY] [public/public/portal.html](file:///f:/Antigravity/Acehack/public/public/portal.html)
- Include the new `<script src="/js/geo-notify.js"></script>` so the tracking continues when users are looking at the transparency map.

## Verification Plan
### Manual Verification
1. Start the server (`npm run dev` or `node server.js`).
2. Open `http://localhost:[port]/` (or [/public/portal.html](file:///f:/Antigravity/Acehack/public/public/portal.html)) in a browser.
3. Allow Location permissions when prompted by the browser.
4. Use the browser's developer tools sensor emulation to mock a GPS location near one of the existing tenders.
5. Verify that the geo-notification toast pops up.
6. Click the action button on the notification and verify it successfully redirects to the complaint submission page with the correct tender ID prefilled in the URL.
